OL,3,CWhy are the US-Iran talks in Islamabad
OL,4,Cso important?
OL,6,FAnd what a challenge lies ahead simply
OL,7,Fto get these talks underway. If, and
OL,8,Fit is still if, they do take place,
OL,9,Faround the table will be
OL,10,Frepresentatives of two countries with
OL,11,Fdecades of loathing, mistrust and
OL,12,Ffailed opportunities to find a
OL,13,Fmutually acceptable way forward.
OL,15,FLet's not forget that some of those
OL,16,Frepresenting Iran are there in part
OL,17,Fbecause America assassinated those who
OL,18,Fwould have been sitting in the same
OL,19,Fchairs. They represent a country and a
OL,20,Fcivilisation which the American
OL,21,Fpresident has threatened to destroy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
