OL,3,CWhy are the US-Iran talks in Islamabad
OL,4,Cso important?
OL,6,FFrom an American point of view, those
OL,7,Fthey deal with are seen as a threat to
OL,8,Fglobal security, with a long history
OL,9,Fof attacks against American citizens
OL,10,Fand assets. They have not crumbled in
OL,11,Fthe face of decades of US attempts to
OL,12,Fbring them down and have proved an
OL,13,Felusive quarry. Furthermore, they now
OL,14,Fhave a stranglehold on the world
OL,15,Feconomy.
OL,17,FMake no mistake, that is why the US
OL,18,Fhas moved to talks.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
